Been/Gone

We use been with the present perfect to talk about visits that were completed.

He's been to the theater three times. 
(He had three visits to the theater.)

They've never been to Canada.

Have you been to the museum?

We use gone with the present perfect to show that someone is on a visit and still away.

She's gone to the shops. 
(She is not here, she is visiting the shops.)

He hasn't gone yet.

They've gone to Mexico on vacation.

Has he gone to Canada.

